Go to https://github.com/.
Signup/Signin.
Add a new project to GitHub repo under the ORGANIZATION. ( Create a new organisation under app repository)

Steps to be followed:

Create an ORGANIZATION.

Create a new repository under the organization. (not under your github username).

Note:
  1. Download the git scm from https://git-scm.com/ which is the client to communicate with the serevr GitHub.com.
  2. Download the tortoiseGit from https://tortoisegit.org/ (this is also a client, just try this. Restart your machine if you don't see the colors on the local repo folders/files.)       
Clone the GitHub repo to your local machine. (using any client Git bash, TortoiseGit, etc)
Syntax: git clone <gitURL> <destinationPath>

Ex: git clone https://github.com/<ORGNAME>/<<Project_Name>>.git <destinationPath>
Configure username & emailid.

git config --global user.email "you@example.com" git config --global user.name "Your Name"

Add the new files/code to repo.

Syantax: git add <fileName>  OR git add .

Ex: git add MyFirstJava.java
Commit to local repo.
Syntax: git commit -m "commit message"

Ex: git commit -m "adding my first project"
Push the commits to server.
Syntax: git push

ex: git push
Do some changes from Server level (Github.com), update your workspace with latest changes.
Synatx: git pull Or git pull origin <branchName>

Ex: git pull origina master
Create a new branch in local and then push your new branch to server.
Syantax: git checkout -b <newBranchName>.
Update two files. Commit each file individually, and see the log locally how the commits created (date & date, commit-id, HEAD, origin branch etc). "git log".

From the above step-10, push only one commit.

Syntax: git push origin <commit-id>:<branchName>
